    "notes": "Asturian accentuation per the Gramática Asturiana (ALLA 2001): written accent wins. Default paroxytone. Words ending in a vowel or -s are paroxytone; words ending in any other consonant (r, l, d, z, x, t, n, m, f) are oxytone. Proparoxytones always carry a written accent. CLITICS: cliticless_words lists the Asturian pallabres atones (Academia de la Llingua Asturiana, Gramatica de la llingua asturiana, prosodia and l'articulu) — articles el/la/lo/los/les, indefinite un/una/unos/unes, the preposition+article contractions al/del/na/nel/pel/polos etc., the atonic prepositions a/de/en/con/por/sin/pa/ente/so, the conjunctions y/o/nin/que/si, and the weak object pronouns me/te/se/y(=lle)/yos/nos/vos/lu/la/los/les. Asturian is enclitic in affirmative finite clauses, but the clitic still bears no word stress."
  },
